summary: It's been one of those days. For once I actually have pretty much all my school work done and because my hands are fucked and I...
body:
It’s been one of those days. For once I actually have pretty much all my school work done and because my hands are fucked and I couldn’t drive to my friends, I have spent the day mostly watching David Tennant as Doctor Who because why the hell not?

So now I have wine, my fur baby’s crate next to me while he sleeps and The Sontaran Stratagem on Netflix. Thank heavens I only have to get through one more week of work and this time next week it will finally be in the holidays and our guests should have buggered off!

blog.name: oimatchstickman
blog.title: Manic Pixie Dream Doctors
blog.description:
A cosplayer, seamstress, and retail worker who has many fictional interests such as: Doctor Who, Phantom of the Opera, Star Trek, Marvel, Portal, Disney, Pixar, Phineas and Ferb, M*A*S*H, Les Miserables, Into the Woods, and any other fandom I feel like.

But mostly Doctor Who.

I like all the Doctor Who I've seen- including Moffat's era- and no hate is tolerated. At all. Let me and others enjoy our show without constantly picking at the smallest thing thanks.

summary: About my earlier post, David Tennant and Peter Davison changing a bulb...this is neither here nor there, and of no importance,...
body:
About my earlier post, David Tennant and Peter Davison changing a bulb…this is neither here nor there, and of no importance, but has the PR policy of The House Of Tennant changed? Previously: zero personal pictures, anecdotes suitable for public, clearly manufactured. Now David speaks of his children in interviews, Georgia publishes family pics on Instagram (even Ty is given some exposure…).

Peter Davison was always a careless talker, there is no restraining him. yes.

But I am just astonished.
